Description: Enable NLA (Network Level Authentication) so mstsc can prompt for credentials.
 KRdp 6.6.4 hardcodes FreeRDP_NlaSecurity to false in src/RdpConnection.cpp,
 which makes the server advertise only plain TLS during RDP security
 negotiation. Microsoft mstsc enforces NLA-required by default on modern
 Windows, so the negotiation fails and mstsc never displays its credential
 prompt. The black-screen flash users see is mstsc completing the TLS
 handshake, then disconnecting because no usable security mode was offered.
 .
 Switching the flag to true makes FreeRDP's server library advertise the
 HYBRID protocol. mstsc shows its native pre-connection credential dialog,
 sends the credentials over CredSSP, and KRdp's existing pamAuthenticate
 path validates them against /etc/pam.d/login. No other code changes
 needed: pam_conv, pam_start("login", ...), and the rest of the auth
 chain were already in place; they just couldn't be reached without NLA.
Author: ConsoleRDP <consolerdp@local>
Forwarded: not-yet
Last-Update: 2026-04-30
Bug-KDE: not-yet (intent to file at https://bugs.kde.org/ once tested)

--- a/src/RdpConnection.cpp
+++ b/src/RdpConnection.cpp
@@ -353,7 +353,7 @@
 
     freerdp_settings_set_bool(settings, FreeRDP_RdpSecurity, false);
     freerdp_settings_set_bool(settings, FreeRDP_TlsSecurity, true);
-    freerdp_settings_set_bool(settings, FreeRDP_NlaSecurity, false);
+    freerdp_settings_set_bool(settings, FreeRDP_NlaSecurity, true);
 
     freerdp_settings_set_uint32(settings, FreeRDP_OsMajorType, OSMAJORTYPE_UNIX);
     // PSEUDO_XSERVER is apparently required for things to work properly.
